Wimbledon tennis men quarter-final as he beat Jan Michael Gambill
July 5.
</P>
<P>
2. A bus is being refueled with compressed natural gas at a gas
station in Jiuzhaigou July 6.
</P>
<P>
3. Chinese President Jiang Zemin shakes hands with Turkmenistan
President Saparmurad Niyazov in Ashkhbad July 6 after signing a
joint statement.
</P>
<P>
4. The world's largest stamp, 32-cm-long and 6-cm-wide,
designed in Beijing, is to be issued worldwide.
</P>
<P>
5. The photo shows Chinese President Jiang Zemin shaking hands
with Russian President Vladimir Putin during a meeting in Dushanbe,
Tajikistan, July 5.
</P>
<P>
6. More tourists visit Dunhuang Mogao Grottoes on the occasion
of the 100th anniversary of the discovery of the Library Grotto.
</P>
<P>
7. The photo shows a Chinese buying condoms at a vending-
machine in Zhengzhou, capital city of central China's Henan
province, July 5.
</P>
<P>
8. The picture shows Chinese President Jiang Zemin addressing a
joint press conference at the fifth summit of the "Shanghai Five"
in Dushanbe, Tajikistan, July 5.
</P>
<P>
9. Students of Shenzhen University for the Aged attended a
computer class July 5.
</P>
<P>
10. Students of Shenzhen University for the Aged attend a
dancing class July 5. 
</P>
