<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Freight Trains Derailed in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Two freight trains were
derailed on the Shijiazhuang-Taiyuan railway this afternoon,
disrupting the operation of the railway.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that a culvert located between the Luquan Station
and Touquan Station caved in, derailing the freight trains that
were running through it.
</P>
<P>
Continuous rainfall over the past few days was responsible for
the caving in, the sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
