<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2030GMT, Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak is urging his
left-wing allies to get mobilized to rally public support for his
peace efforts as he prepares to leave for a pivotal three-way
summit in the United States.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with One Israel ministers on Thursday, Barak said
he regrets that the left is not organizing demonstrations or
raising posters to show support publicly for the peace process and
he is worried that right-wing activists will be the only presence
on the streets to make themselves seen and heard. (BC-Israel-Public
Support-Summit)
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak is determined to
proceed with a planned pivotal three-way summit starting Tuesday in
the United States despite resignation threats of three right-wing
partners in his coalition government, Israel Radio quoted sources
close to Barak as saying on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Barak is meeting leaders of the left-wing Meretz party regarding
the upcoming summit between himself, Palestinian leader Yasser
Arafat and U.S. President Bill Clinton at Camp David, a
presidential resort in Maryland, the radio said. (BC-Israel-PM-
Summit)
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- U.N. Middle East envoy Terje Roed Larsen arrived in
Lebanon Friday to present a modified map of Blue Line to Lebanese
officials to clear up Israel's continuing violations of the border.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. official, accompanied by the U.N.'s chief cartographer
Miklos Pinther, talked with Lebanese leaders on some changes of the
Blue Line drawn by U.N. experts according to the 1923 Lebanese-
Palestinian boundary.
</P>
<P>
U.N. Interim Force in Lebanon (UNIFIL), which has been deployed
in south Lebanon since 1978 after Israel launched a 90-day war to
Lebanon, reported 12 Israeli violations of the Blue Line to the U.
N. Security Council on Monday. (BC-Lebanon-UN-Blue Line)
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Two reformist parties in Iran on Friday urged
government agencies to make thorough investigations into a student
dormitory incident that sparked nation-wide riots last July.
</P>
<P>
The roots of the incident must be found out and all persons
responsible should be identified and punished, said a statement
issued by the Islamic Labor Party on the occasion of the first
anniversary of the incident.
</P>
<P>
It added that merely trying some soldiers and police commanders
are far from being enough, because the people want those behind the
scenes to be exposed.(BC-Iran-Dormitroy Accident) 
</P>
</TEXT>
