<HEADLINE> NAFTA Is First importer of Uruguayan Meat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The exports to the NAFTA countries -- Canada, Mexico and the
United States -- amounted to 60,000 tons during the first semester
of this year, almost double than the same period of 1999, said the
institute in a document published Friday in the press.
</P>
<P>
Meat exports to NAFTA surpassed from July of 1999 to June of
this year 100,000 tons, with a value above 100 million U.S.
dollars, said the institute in a document published Friday.
</P>
<P>
Canada is he main destination of the Uruguayan beef exports,
and Mexico the second, with an equal growth of 400 percent over
the previous 12-month period from July of 1998 to June of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Uruguayan exports in the first six months of this year amounted
to 146,894 tons of beef and 9,309 tons of mutton, worth 250
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The European Union was for a long time the main market for
Uruguayan meat, but it lost this position in the last seasons.
