genocide to take place. They failed to do so," said the committee
in its 318-page report.
</P>
<P>
The report, entitled "Rwanda: the Preventable Genocide," was
drawn up by seven individuals headed by former Botswana President
Ketumile Masire. The group as formed by the OAU in 1998 to
investigate the causes of the genocide in Rwanda and make
