<HEADLINE> Internet Users in Greece to Increase Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Greece's Internet users are
expected to increase from this year's 800,000 to 3.5 million by
2004, according to a survey conducted by the ICAP-Focus-Bari
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The survey attributed the expected significant growth in
Internet users in coming years to the result of the creation of
Greek portals offering a wide range of information applications in
the Greek language and the development of the wireless technology.
</P>
<P>
Greece' portals in the Internet would be raised from three to
10 next year.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Greek Internet users were focusing on obtaining
information and news, with only a small percentage using its
electronic commerce services.
</P>
<P>
Greece lags the other European countries in information
technology and telecommunications spending and ranked at the
bottom of the table with 567 euros per capital last year.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, Greece's average Internet penetration rate was 6.0
percent.
</P>
<P>
The survey said that Greece's low Internet penetration rate
was the result of the high access costs paid for computers,
limited technological infrastructure and high access costs paid by
Internet users in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
