<HEADLINE> Forest Fires Reported Throughout Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Several forest fires were reported
throughout Greece Friday, with the largest blaze being on the
eastern Aegean island of Samos.
</P>
<P>
With the support of fire-fighting planes and helicopters, some
200 firefighters with 30 fire engines were trying hard to bring a
major fire in Samos under control, the semi-official Athens News
Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
In the Attica prefecture, a fire was ravaging woods at the
Souli site near Marathon, and other blazes were reported at the
Kissavos site in the central Greek prefecture of Magnesia, in the
Gerolimena on the southeastern Peloponnese peninsula and in the
Achaia prefecture.
</P>
<P>
Although the Greek government has since April taken preventive
measures to deal with possible forest fires, the forest land
destruction in the country increased 300 percent in June compared
to last year.
</P>
<P>
Police attributed the forest fires to both the current high
temperatures and arsons. 
</P>
