<HEADLINE> Traffic Accident Kills 42 in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- An overloaded truck ran out of the
road in Angola's south central Huila province, killing 42 and
injuring 34, the Angolan official news agency Angop reported on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to a report issued by Angop without mentioning the
date, the accident occurred when a Volvo-brand truck ran out of
the road and overturned.
</P>
<P>
Angop quoted an eye-witness of the disaster as saying that the
cause of the accident could be the excessive cargo loaded and the
intoxication of the driver.
</P>
<P>
Road traffic has been rehabilitated in some central provinces
after government troops gained victory in the central highland
late last year.
</P>
<P>
However, the safety of the road traffic is considered as
worrying due to the enormous destruction of the roads and bridges
by rampant battles between government troops and the rebel
National Union for the Total Independence of Angola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
