<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Parliament Speaker
Dawit Yohannes said here on Friday that Ethiopia will concentrate
its efforts on developing national economy now that its war
against Eritrea has come to an end.
</P>
<P>
"It is clear now that the situation between Ethiopia and
Eritrea has gone beyond the military face.The issue now is to
obtain comprehensive peace agreement so that we can concentrate on
our development," he told Xinhua.
</P>
