<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Federation Council, the
upper house of parliament, approved Mikhail Kislitsyn, prosecutor
of Moscow's Military District, as the country's chief military
prosecutor Friday.
</P>
<P>
The house endorsed Kislitsyn's appointment at its extraordinary
session by a vote of all 136 senators "for", just hours after
Prosecutor General Vladimir Ustinov nominated Kislitsyn.
</P>
