<HEADLINE> Agnolutto Wins Seventh Stage of Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Christophe Agnolutto of France won
the 205.5-kilometer seventh stage of the Tour de France cycle race
from Tours to Limoges on Friday.
</P>
<P>
30-year-old Agnolutto riding for the AG2R team and a former
winner of the Tour of Switzerland, won with a startling 128km solo
ride to become the first French stage winner since 1998.
</P>
<P>
Agnolutto finished one minute 11 seconds ahead of the peloton
with German Marcel Wust taking second while compatriot Erik Zabel
came in third.
</P>
<P>
Zabel's Telekom teammate Italian Alberto Elli retained the
overall leader's yellow jersey. 
