<HEADLINE> College Entrance Exams Start Amid Expectations (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Starting today, millions of Chinese
families will spend a weekend full of expectations.
</P>
<P>
They all hope their children will pass the three-day national
college entrance examinations.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Yuan is one of the 3.88 million examinees this year. There
are about 500,000 more entrants than last year. The 19-year-old
Beijing girl will have a 50-50 chance of being enrolled by a
Chinese college or university.
</P>
<P>
"My dream is to enter Beijing University and major in
international finance, though I know it will be a hard challenge
because it's also the dream of many others," says Zhou.
</P>
<P>
Hot targets chased by the young examinees also include
economics, computer technology and foreign languages.
</P>
<P>
"Children like my daughter have many more opportunities than we
had," says Zhou's mother Shan Guoxia, who accompanied her daughter
to the Beijing No. 101 Middle School to take the exam this morning.
</P>
