<HEADLINE> Senior Official Calls for Ethical and Cultural Progress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official called
today for concrete efforts to promote ethical and cultural
progress as the country is putting emphasis on ideological and
political work.
</P>
<P>
Ding Guan'gen, director of the Central Commission for Guiding
Ethical and Cultural Progress, told a meeting of the commission
here today that top leader Jiang Zemin's recent speech on
ideological and political work is of great significance for the
country's ethical and cultural progress.
</P>
<P>
Promotion of ethical and cultural progress must follow the
spirit of Jiang's speech and stick to Marxism, Leninism, Mao
Zedong Thought and Deng Xiaoping Theory, said Ding, also a member
of the Political Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
It is imperative to have more ideological and ethical education,
make socialist ethics dominate the ideological and cultural fronts,
and meet the growing spiritual and cultural demands of the general
public, Ding said.
</P>
<P>
At today's meeting, the participants also discussed the
commission's "Suggestions on Building Ethical and Cultural
Progress Communities in Urban Areas." 
