<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU, Angola Sign Protocol on Fisheries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Angola and the European Union (EU)
have signed in Luanda a protocol on fisheries, paving the way for
EU countries to develop fishing activities in the Angolan sea
areas, the official newspaper Jornal de Angola reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Angolan minister of fisheries Fatima Jardim and head of the EU
delegation Emilio Mastracchio signed the accord, which will allow
some 70 fishing boats from the EU to conduct activities within the
Angolan sea territory for two years.
</P>
<P>
The accord foresees the reinforcement of cooperation between
the two sides in implementing action programs on research and
evaluation of halieutic resources, with an aim to improve the
preservation and the rational management.
</P>
<P>
The betterment of the quality of marine products, the check-up
on fishing activities and the development of professional training
are also part of the program to be implemented under the accord.
</P>
<P>
During the negotiation, Jardim stressed the importance of the
cooperation between the Angolan government and the EU, expressing
hope to see the partner much more engaged in the projects on
fisheries and environment.
</P>
<P>
In his turn, Mastracchio showed interest in the continuation of
the protocol on fisheries with Angola, highlighting the Angolan
government's efforts in the process of restoring peace and
economic development around the war-torn country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
