<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Early Tour de France Doping Tests Negative </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 7 (Xinhua) -- All doping tests on the first three
stages of the Tour de France cycle race were negative, the
International Cycling Union (UCI) said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The UCI noted that substances like corticoids had been detected
in the urine samples of some riders but that their presence was "
justified by medical prescriptions".
</P>
<P>
Three riders were sent home before the start of the Tour after
blood tests found they had an illegal level of hematocrite.
</P>
<P>
All riders tested on this Tour will also have their urine
samples kept for further analysis when a new EPO test receives an
official go-ahead, probably before the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
On the Tour, the yellow jersey wearer, the stage winner and two
riders drawn at random have their urine tested at the end of each
stage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
