<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Sautin Snatches Second European Diving Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Dmitry Sautin of Russia took his
second diving gold in two days at the European swimming
championships on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Sautin, who won his three-meter springboard title on Thursday,
shared an overwhelming victory with Igor Lukashin in Friday's
synchronised 10-meter platform final.
</P>
<P>
The Russian pair totalled 323.46 points from their five dives
to win by a big margin from Ukrainians Roman Volodkov and
Oleksandr Skrypnik (292.74) and Britain's Peter Waterfield and
Leon Taylor (280.20).
</P>
<P>
Sautin, world champion on both the three-meter and 10-meter
boards, also took a Helsinki silver on Tuesday when he partnered
Alexander Dobroskok to second place in the synchronised three-
meter springboard event.
</P>
<P>
Sautin will defend his individual platform title at the weekend.
</P>
</TEXT>
