<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Exhibition of Contemporary French Art Held in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 7 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition of contemporary French
art was launched Friday at the Macao Museum of Art.
</P>
<P>
On display are more than 50 items of artistic works created by
11 artists living in Nice City of France. The exhibition will last
till September 3.
</P>
<P>
Nice is a coastal city situated in the southern part of France,
where sunny climate and picturesque views provide an ideal
environment for creative motivation.
</P>
<P>
A number of great artists used to visit the place and made
outstanding achievements. Their radiance, however, became a
barrier for young artists who were hesitant to go forward with
their own ambitions. The problem was how to get away from the huge
shadows of their predecessors.
</P>
<P>
Beginning from the mid-1950s, some young artists gradually
formed the schools of "New Realism," "Supports/Surface" and "
Fluxus." The schools produced not only works of art, but also
confidence and courage to struggle against traditional bondage.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
