<HEADLINE> MILF Claims Shooting Down Philippine Military Chopper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- A Philippine military chopper was
reportedly shot down Friday afternoon by the Moro Islamic
Liberation Front (MILF), amid offensives by government troops on
MILF's main camp, a TV report said.
</P>
<P>
MILF spokesperson Eid Kabalu was quoted as saying when making
this claim that they are fiercely defending their main stronghold
Camp Abubakar against military air and ground attacks, the ABS-CBN
news channel said.
</P>
<P>
However, the military denied Kabalu's claim, calling it a rebel
propaganda.
</P>
<P>
"That's Kabalu's propaganda. He is dreaming; he should wake up,
" the government military spokesman Rafael Romero said in reaction
to Kabalu's claim.
</P>
<P>
But Kabalu said the chopper was shot down between 1 p.m. and 1:
30 p.m., saying he witnessed its plunge into the sea in Calatagan,
South Lanao province.
</P>
<P>
Soldiers in the chopper have yet to be accounted for, but
Kabalu said they were most likely killed.
</P>
<P>
The MILF spokesman said they used home-made anti-aircaft
ammunition to shoot down the supposed MG-520 chopper of the Armed
Forces of Philippines (AFP).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the military admitted Friday that Camp Abubakar is
indeed under attack and its fall is imminent.
</P>
<P>
The military spokesman said the strategy is to take Abubakar,
the largest camp of the MILF, "swiftly and as soon as possible."
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, government forces reportedly captured three more
MILF camps near Abubakar.
</P>
<P>
Starting from the beginning of this week, the government troops
have launched air and ground attack at the secessionist group's
biggest camp.
</P>
<P>
The latest fighting came after the government and the MILF
failed to sign an interim peace accord before the June 30 deadline
set by President Joseph Estrada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
