<HEADLINE> Prices of Gold, Silver Down in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Standard gold and twenty-two-carat gold both edged down by 10
rupees (0.23 U.S. dollar) to close at 4,550 rupees (103.41 dollars)
and 4,210 rupees (95.68 dollars) per 10 grams respectively from 4,
560 rupees (103.64 dollars) and 4,220 rupees (95.91 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, ready silver (.999 fineness) fell by 20 rupees (0.45
dollar) to close at 7,970 rupees (181.14 dollars) per kilogram
from 7,990 rupees (181.59 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) also closed lower at 7,835 rupees (
178.07 dollars) per kg from 7,865 rupees (178.75 dollars). 
