<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Rupiah Continues to Weaken </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian currency Rupiah
continued its weakening trend on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah traded at 9,305 (buying) and 9,315 (selling) per U.S.
dollar on Friday, compared with 9,270/9,300 per dollar on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Finance Minister Bambang Sudibyo Friday admitted that the
weakening of the rupiah exchange rate to more than 9,000 rupiah to
the dollar would have a bad impact upon the country's bid for
economic recovery.
</P>
<P>
"But, we expect the rupiah to rebound soon because the problem
is only a matter of perception regarding political stability in
Indonesia," he said on the sidelines of a House Special Committee
meeting deliberating a Tax Bill.
</P>
<P>
Bank Indonesia has said that the current weakening of the
rupiah has been largely due to domestic political uncertainty,
particularly in the run-up to the General Session of the People's
Consultative Assembly in August. 
</P>
</TEXT>
