<HEADLINE> Shanghai Starts to Build China's Largest Knitted Goods Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Work began today in Shanghai on
the construction of what is expected to be China's largest
production base for knitted goods.
</P>
<P>
The "Three Gun Industrial Park," with a total investment of 280
million yuan (about 3.5 million U.S. dollars), occupies an area of
15 hectares. It will produce 30 million sq m of knitted materials
for outer garments and 50 million pieces of knitted underwear.
</P>
<P>
The base will pay particular attention to environmental
protection by setting up a waste water treatment system, according
to company officials.
</P>
<P>
This is another effort by Shanghai to update its low-efficiency
and polluting textile industry and protect the environment.
</P>
<P>
So far, about 500 factories have been relocated because of
pollution, being permitted to reopen in the suburbs after
installing anti-pollution devices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
