<DOCNO> XIE20000707.0111 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore PM Warns against Erosion of Community Bonding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok
Tong has warned against erosion of community bonding in the New
Economy society and urged Singaporeans to promote volunteerism.
</P>
<P>
"Unless we make a conscious effort, our economic success could
gradually erode the sense of empathy for the less fortunate among
us, and lead to a colder, less caring society," the prime minister
said while officiating at opening the National Volunteer Center
Friday.
</P>
<P>
He said the challenge for the Singapore society is to improve
on the present level of community spirit, mentioning a survey
which proves 74 percent of non-volunteers cited "no time" due to
work and family commitments as their main reason for not
volunteering.
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged that both the government and people have a role
to play in promoting volunteerism, saying "the moral test of any
society is how it treats its weakest: children, elderly, sick,
needy and handicapped."
</P>
<P>
He said the government cannot artificially narrow the income
but can put in place schemes to assist the needy in areas such as
education, housing and healthcare and will ensure that "every
Singaporean has equal opportunity to rise to the top."
</P>
<P>
He urged those who have benefited from the general increase in
prosperity in Singapore to reciprocate society.
</P>
<P>
The National Volunteer Center (NVC) is a national-level
coordinating agency for volunteerism in Singapore and works in
partnership with the public, private and people sectors to make
volunteerism a way of life in the city state.
</P>
<P>
NVC is engaged in volunteer promotion, referral, appreciation,
management and training and aims to help strengthen Singapore's
social cohesion, political stability and the collective will,
values and attitudes of the people through its mission of
promoting volunteerism across all sectors and all levels of the
society. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
