<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK's Foreign Reserve Amounts to 97.1 Billion U.S. Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The official foreign currency
reserve assets of Hong Kong amounted to 97.1 billion U.S. dollars
at the end of June 2000 from 95.2 billion U.S. dollars at the end
of May, announced the Hong Kong Monetary Authority Friday.
</P>
<P>
In terms of foreign currency reserves ranking, Hong Kong is the
world's fourth largest holder of foreign currency reserves after
Japan, China's mainland and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The total foreign currency reserve assets of 97.1 billion U.S.
dollars represent over seven times the currency in circulation or
about 40 percent of Hong Kong dollar M3, one of the highest ratios
in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
