<HEADLINE> China's Largest Thermal Power Generating Unit Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The first 800,000-kw thermal power
generating unit of the Suizhong Generating Company in northeast
China's Liaoning Province, the largest of its kind in China,
started producing electricity today.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the project at a cost of 10 billion yuan (
about 1.2 billion U.S. dollars) started in 1993. A total of four
units imported from Russia with an aggregate generating capacity
of 3.2 million kw are being installed.
</P>
<P>
The company is the key power plant connecting two major
electricity networks in northeast China and north China. 
</P>
