<HEADLINE> HR Staff Spend Five Hours On Net Daily: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Human Resource (HR) professionals
spend as much as five hours daily on the Internet and related e-
mail and believe the Internet will continue to grow in importance
to their profession, according to a recent survey by William M.
Mercer, operator of a HR website in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The survey involved 210 HR professionals from all over Asia.
Ninety-one percent of the respondents were local citizens and nine
percent were expatriates from over 200 companies.
</P>
<P>
Every respondent indicates they have access to the Internet, e-
mail or their company's Intranet at home or work. Forty-four
percent of them say they use the Internet daily while a whopping
71 expect using it daily in the near future.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 percent of the respondents who use the net are
over 35 years of age, with 27 percent in 35-39 age group and 18
percent in the 40-49 age group.
</P>
<P>
The findings is contrary to the commonly believed notion that
the Internet is the preserve of the younger generation, according
to William M. Mercer.
</P>
<P>
More than 75 percent of respondents want to find more concrete
HR services on the Internet, in addition to the most common
application for HR professionals of online recruitment.
</P>
<P>
HR professionals also expressed their desire to get useful HR
information, case studies, references, publications and advices on
the Internet, according to the survey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000707.0141 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Legislature Passes Law on Science, Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Legislative Council of the Macao
Special Administrative Region (SAR) has approved a law to promote
the development of science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Passed by the legislature Thursday, the Law of Program for
Science and Technology stipulates that the SAR government shall
establish a special fund to encourage scientific and technological
research and the application of scientific achievements.
</P>
<P>
The government should also be responsible for promoting the
education of scientific knowledge in a bid to raise scientific and
technological awareness among local residents, especially the
young people.
</P>
<P>
Containing 11 articles, the law covers the freedom of
scientific and technological research, research organizations,
researchers, fund for scientific and technological development,
international scientific and technological cooperation and
exchange, and education on scientific knowledge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
