<HEADLINE> Skate-bikes Popular Among Macao Youngsters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Skate-bikes have become popular
gadgets among youngsters in Macao in recent months.
</P>
<P>
Japan is believed to be the source to pass on the trendy thing
to Macao in April. One skate-bike used to cost as much as 1,300
patacas (about 160 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The skate-bikes were mainly imported from Switzerland and China
's inland areas and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Fierce market competition has pulled prices down. Now skate-
bikes can be bought with only 200 patacas (25 U.S. dollars) or
less.
</P>
<P>
Skate-bikes are normally made of aluminum, iron or alloy. Many
youngsters like to paint colors to make their bikes more
attractive. Some do-it-yourself lovers can even experience a
speedy fun by installing an electric motor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
