<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Sharply Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed sharply
up 340.37 points, or 2.06 percent, at 16,829.96 Friday.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market sentiment was helped at the outset by a
2.52 percent jump in the Nasdaq composite index overnight. China
Mobile, formerly known as China Telecom, was leading the market
higher while Cable &AMP; Wireless HKT, PCCW and Hutchison Whampoa
continued to gain grounds.
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices, Utilities dropped 1.34 percent, but
Finance, Properties and Industry &AMP; Commerce rose 0.53 percent, 2.
32 percent and 3.02 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 11.866 billion HK dollars (1.521 billion U.S.
dollars), compared to Thursday's 12.273 billion HK dollars (1.573
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
China-related stocks ended with the Hang Seng China Enterprises
Index down 1.54 percent, but the Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corp
Index up 0.66 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index and the Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index
also increased by 3.58 percent and 1.36 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
In the whole week, Hong Kong stocks opened slightly up 21.28
points, or 0.13 percent, at 16,177.06 on Monday and continued
rising day after day, closing sharply higher at 16,829.96 on
Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
