<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Weaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar fell half a
U.S. cent Friday as the market was nervous about the speculation
that the U.S. Federal Reserve would raise interest rates again.
</P>
<P>
The currency hit a low of 58.65 U.S. cents this afternoon and
it firmed slightly before the close to end the local session at 58.
74, from 59.15 the previous day.
</P>
<P>
Any increase in the Australia/U.S. interest rate differential
would hurt the local currency because it lures investment away
from Australian dollar bonds and deposits.
</P>
<P>
Australian interest rates are at 6.0 percent while the U.S.
dollar's are at 6.5 percent. 
</P>
