five percent, to 17.15 Australian dollars and NAB jumped 46 cents
to 26.15 Australian dollars. ANZ up 11 cents to 12.61 Australian
dollars, and Westpac edged 3.6 cents higher to 11.826 Australian
dollars. The Commonwealth fell 19.4 cents to 27.166 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The strongest sector was resources. Rio Tinto surged 87.8 cents
to 26.858 Australian dollars and BHP closed at 18.936 Australian
dollars, up 8.6 cents for the day.
</P>
<P>
News Corp ordinary shares dropped 44 cents to 22.70 Australian
dollars and its preferred scrip declined 30.8 cents to 19.552
Australian dollars. PBL fell 24.4 cents to 13.50 Australian
dollars. 
