<HEADLINE> Tri-motorcar Overturn Kills 10 in Sichuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Ten people were killed and six
injured Thursday after a three-wheeled motorcar overturned and
plunged into a pond in Leshan City, in Sichuan Province of
southwest China, local authorities said today.
</P>
<P>
The vehicle, traditionally used for farming purposes, was
overloaded with 19 farmers when it lost control on a rise on a
mountainous section of road in Jianwei County and slid into a pond
30 meters below.
</P>
<P>
One of the six injured passengers remains in serious condition
at a local hospital.
</P>
<P>
Police said the driver had no operator's license and his
vehicle was not registered. He has been detained by police for
questioning. 
