<HEADLINE> Chinese Treasuries Hovers On Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese treasuries kept hovering
around the current prices on thin trading on Friday, with trading
volume expanding to 1.6 billion yuan, up 120 million from
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Half of the six current bonds declined with losses ranging from
0.01 percent to 0.12 percent while the remaining three, 000696,
009905 and 010004 with floating interest rates, edged up narrowly
by 0.08 percent on average.
</P>
<P>
Starting from this quarter, securities investment funds have
been gradually transferring money away from treasuries into the
equity market for higher investment returns. These big players
seem pretty indifferent to current treasuries while focusing their
attention on the more bullish China's stock market, according to
Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory
company.
</P>
<P>
Lack of impetus, the trade volume on the three-day, seven-day,
14-day and 28-day repo transactions contracted by 1.27 billion
yuan further to 5.47 billion. The interest rate on the three-day
transaction dipped by 2.73 percentage points to 1.02 percent,
Homeway said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
