<HEADLINE> Four Cult Members Nabbed in S. Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Police arrested four members of a
Christian cult Tuesday night for desecrating graves in a public
cemetery in the southern Philippine city of Cagayan de Oro, a TV
report said Friday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The suspects are reportedly members of the Democratic
Brotherhood Crusader Divine Healing-Haring Bakal, a Christian cult
based in Davao City, the country's leading news channel ABS-CBN
said.
</P>
<P>
The suspects were caught by local policemen removing the
kneecaps from the skeletons in two graves at a public cemetery in
Cagayan de Oro, capital city of Misamis Oriental province.
</P>
<P>
Found in their possession were forty two kneecaps, amulets and
several small bottles of oil, ABS-CBN added. 
