<HEADLINE> Shenzhen A-share Market Edges Up at Friday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen composite index closed
at 601.65 points on Friday, up 5.35 points or 0.9 percent from the
last close. The sub-index closed at 4751.99 points, up 40.18
points from yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover stood at 9.36 billion yuan (1.13 billion U.S.
dollars), 1.6 percent more than yesterday's 9.21 billion.
</P>
<P>
State-owned big-cap stocks performed actively and became market
bellwethers, as their interim results were well expected,
according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and
securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
According to Wall Street investment firm Merrill Lynch, China's
stock market soared 47 percent in the first half of 2000, becoming
the best global performer.
</P>
<P>
The first listed company's interim report was released on the
Shanghai Stock Exchange this morning by Lanzhou Minbai
Shareholding (Group) Co. Ltd. The company's profit was 9.277
million yuan in the first half of this year, of which 300 million
was earned from its investment. The company's earning per share
was 0.079 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The newly listed company, Chengzhi Shareholding Co. Ltd was the
top gainer with its price up 10.02 percent to its ceiling 29.22
yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
The Sichuan Golden Summit (Group) Joint-Stock Co. Ltd was the
biggest loser, with price dropping 9.96 percent to 10.85 yuan per
share.
</P>
<P>
The market is likely to try a new high next week, Homeway
analysts predicted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
