<HEADLINE> Shenzhen B-share Market Up at Friday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen B-share market
recouped most of yesterday's steep losses and launched a solid
move on Friday, gaining the 110-point level toward the close of
trading.
</P>
<P>
The B-share index firmed 1.93 points or 1.78 percent, to the
intraday high at 110.49.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover was 63.50 million HK dollars, 77.8 million
HK dollars or 55.06 percent less than Thursday's total.
</P>
<P>
Opening on a positive note, the market headed for a significant
reversal in the wake of two straight days of negativity with some
defending buyer on the heels of trading interest in late afternoon.
But investors' activity remained subdued toward the end of the
week, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and
securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Gainers outnumbered losers by 38 to 10, with 7 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Shenbao Inc jumped 10.03 percent to 3.5 HK dollars, while
Huaxin Pack added 5.45 percent to 2.13 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
Benelux Enter shed 3.89 percent to 2.47 HK dollars while Shzh
Tellus dipped 2.29 percent to 1.71 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
Limited action may persist for another couple of days with the
overall marketplace not running aggressively due to the
uncertainty surrounding corporate earnings.  
</P>
</TEXT>
