<HEADLINE> No Group in Indonesia Able to Launch Coup D'etat: Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Defense Minister Juwono
Sudarsono said here Friday there is no single group in the country
that will be able to launch a coup d'etat against President
Abdurrahman Wahid, including military.
</P>
<P>
"I can say that there is no single group in the country which
could launch a coup d'etat against the government, including
military, as they were devided in groups," Sudarsono told Xinhua
in an exclusive interview.
</P>
<P>
He also admitted that currently the Indonesian Military (TNI)
also has been devided in groups, but he was optimistic such a
thing will be ended when "the younger generations replace the old
ones."
</P>
<P>
"There is a pro-status-quo group and a pro-reforms group, so I
could say that there is not a strong group that may be able to
launch a coup d'etat," he reiterated.
</P>
<P>
Sudarsono also said that pro-status-quo group has been
hammering out a scenario to unseat incumbent President Abdurrahman
Wahid.
</P>
<P>
"And the people of status quo, and I can say they are cronies
of former President Soeharto, want to hamper the process of
investigation into former President Soeharto. They are afraid of
being brought to justice," the minister added.
</P>
<P>
"They are trying to do anything they could to hamper the
investigation process (into Soeharto for corruption cases) by
inciting riots and finance communal bloodshed," he added.
</P>
<P>
"And they have a main target namely creating an impression that
the government is not capable to deal with the situation, and at
last, they want to topple President Wahid," Sudarsono said.
</P>
<P>
He denied suggestions that the ongoing riots and communal
bloodshed which have been taking place in some parts of the
country were designed by the TNI.
</P>
<P>
"That is not possible. TNI is not able to make such a design,
moreover a grand ones," he said. 
