<HEADLINE> Turkmenistan's Grain Yield Hits Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Turkmenistan has harvested 1.7
million tons of grain after the summer crown of this year, up 0.2
million tons from the expected amount, breaking the country's
record of grain yield for the whole year, according to latest
media reports reaching here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The grain production target for this year was surpassed in late
June, while in the same time of last year only about 1 million
tons of grain were harvested, the reports quoted the Turkmenistani
Agriculture Ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
Last year's total grain harvest amounted to 1.51 million tons,
it said.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, Turkmenistani President Saparmurad Niyazov told a
cabinet meeting that 1.8 million tons of grain will be produced in
2001, ensuring the country full food security in the next two
years.
</P>
<P>
A program of Turkmenistan's social and economic development for
2000-2010 and the national goal of food safety stipulate a grain
production of 2.5 million tons in 2003, 3 million in 2005, and 5
million in 2010.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, Turkmenistan, which has been buying grain
and flour from neighboring countries, will be able to export about
2.5 million tons of grain by 2010. 
</P>
</TEXT>
