<HEADLINE> Highway to Designed Hydropower Station on Hongshui River Opens to Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- A highway designed to facilitate
construction of the Longtan Hydropower Station on Hongshui River,
south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, has been completed
and opened to traffic.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the 81 km highway connects Tian'e
County, where the hydropower station will be located, with Nandan
County, also in Guangxi.
</P>
<P>
Longtan Hydropower Station is one of the key projects designed
to develop water resources on the Hongshui River. It will have a
generating capacity of 5.4 million kw, second only to the Three
Gorges Hydropower Project on the mighty Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the principal works for Longtan Hydropower
Station, involving a total investment of some 30 billion yuan (3.
61 billion U.S. dollars), will start this year, said the sources.
</P>
