<HEADLINE> Missing Person in Guangdong Bus Crash Confirmed Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 7 (Xinhua) -- One person missing after a bus
crash on July 1 in Guangdong Province has been confirmed dead,
raising the death toll from the accident to 14.
</P>
<P>
The body of the missing person, identified as the bus driver,
Zhong Zhiwen, was found at noon Thursday in the reservoir of the
Qiaonan Power Station in Ruyuan County.
</P>
<P>
Following the crash, Shaoguan police and communications
departments have launched an investigation into road safety in
mountainous area and tourism zones.
</P>
<P>
The bus carrying 20 people swerved off a road in Ruyuan County,
Shaoguan city, and plunged 600 feet (200 meters) into a ravine.
The vehicle was traveling to a scenic spot near the ravine.
</P>
<P>
Local people rushed to the rescue, while some 60 workers used
knives and axes to cut a road through the dense forest in the
hilly area and sent six badly-injured passengers to hospital.
</P>
<P>
The injured are in stable condition, according to hospital
reports. 
</P>
