<HEADLINE> Shanghai B-share Market Up at Friday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai B-share market index
rose 0.48 points, or 0.89 percent, to 54.86 at the close on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover stood at 11.14 million U.S. dollars (92.46 million
yuan), which was 4 million U.S. dollars or 26.42 percent less than
Thursday's total.
</P>
<P>
After a flat open today, the market drilled steadily on to
stage a sudden rally in the last hour of trading in the morning
session. But it pared some of its gains in the late afternoon, as
investors' activity remained subdued toward the end of the week.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outpaced declining shares by 34 to 11. with 9
unchanged, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial
and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Rubber Belt added 4.62 percent to 0.272 U.S. dollars, while
Vacuum &AMP; Elect rose 3.95 percent to 0.474 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
ST Ch Text Mach slipped 4.62 percent to 0.164 U.S. dollars,
while Ch 1st Pencil fell 3.88 percent to 0.248 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Limited action may persist for another couple of days with the
overall marketplace not come running aggressively due to the
uncertainty surrounding corporate earnings, Home analysts said.
</P>
</TEXT>
