<HEADLINE> Shanghai A-share Market Closes Strongly on Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai composite index closed
at 1932.61 points on Friday, up 28.61 points or 1.5 percent,
compared to the last close.
</P>
<P>
The total trading volume was 10.21 billion yuan (1.23 billion U.
S. dollars), 21.84 percent more than the previous session's 8.38
billion yuan, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line
financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai composite index edged up strongly at the end of
this week. The state-owned big-cap stocks performed actively and
became market bellwethers, as their interim results were well
expected.
</P>
<P>
According to Wall Street investment firm Merrill Lynch, China's
stock market soared 47 percent in the first half of 2000, becoming
the best global performer.
</P>
<P>
The first listed company's interim report was released this
morning by Lanzhou Minbei Shareholding (Group) Co., Ltd. The
company's profit was 9.277 million yuan in the first half of this
year, of which 300 million yuan was earned from its investment
income. The company's earnings per share was 0.079 yuan. The
company's price slightly edged down by 0.24 yuan or 1.62 percent
to 14.58 yuan per share, when it was resumed this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
China Eastern Airlines Corporation Ltd., Lingyuan Steel and
other three companies were top gainers today. Their prices rose 10
percent to their ceilings.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan Malong Chemicals &AMP; Construction Co., Ltd. was the
biggest loser with its price down 10 percent to the floor 23.76
yuan per share, hit by selling pressure.
</P>
<P>
The market is likely to try a new high next week, Homeway
analysts predicted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
