<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Plays Significant Role in Asia: Indonesian Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- A senior Indonesian official said
here Friday that China plays a significant role in maintaining the
political and security stability in the Asian region and hoped its
role will be maintained in the future.
</P>
<P>
"Yes, it is clear that China has played a significant role in
creating stability in the region. And we hope the role will be
maintained in the future," Indonesian Defense Minister Juwono
Sudarsono said in an exclusive interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"China and other big countries in the region such as India and
Japan also have to maintain their roles in creating stability in
Asia," he added.
</P>
<P>
Considering the Taiwan issue as an internal affair of the
Chinese government, Sudarsono hoped that it will be handled well.
</P>
<P>
"We leave such a matter to those who are concerned, namely the
Chinese government. We will not make any intervention in their
domestic affairs," he said, hoping that relationship between
Indonesia and China will be better and better in the future.
</P>
<P>
In connection with the Association of Southeast Asian Nation (
ASEAN), the minister hoped that China will be more active in
holding dialogues (with ASEAN members).
</P>
<P>
"And we want that China will also be more active in talks with
Indonesia through ASEAN," Sudarsono said, adding that the
relations between China and ASEAN members could also be
strengthened.
</P>
<P>
"Beside China, we also hope that Japan and India will join
hands to build what I call as an Asian identity based on the
dignity and cultural principles of Asian nations," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We also have to consider creating a joint preventive measures
strategy, involving China, Japan, India, Indonesia and other big
countries in the region (to prevent possible threats from outside
region)," he said.
</P>
<P>
"But we don't hope that Asia will be an exclusive region. Our
relations with Asian countries should be strengthened, but we also
have to maintain our relations with countries outside Asia, such
as the United States," Sudarsono added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
