<HEADLINE> Traffic Accident Kills 27 in Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, July 7 (Xinhua) -- A truck ran into a bus near the
northern Spanish city of Soria Thursday, killing at least 27
people and injuring 13, police said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Police said the truck, loaded with pork, suddenly drove out of
its lane and knocked into the bus carrying 39 teenagers from the
opposite direction before the two vehicles fell into a ditch by
the road, killing 22 people on the spot. Five more people died in
hospital later.
</P>
<P>
Police said most of the victims were high school students aged
between 13 and 15. The two drivers were also killed.
</P>
<P>
The students reportedly came from Barcelona and were taking
their vacation in Soria.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident was not immediately known.
</P>
<P>
Authorities said the crash was one of the two worst accidents
in the last five years in Spain. In September 1999, 28 people were
killed when a bus on a regular run between Madrid and Gerona in
northwestern Spain overturned near Zaragoza. 
</P>
</TEXT>
