<HEADLINE> Indonesia Lists 20 Boxers For President Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian Amateur Boxing
Association (Pertina) has selected 20 boxers from the recent
National Sports Championship to be included in the President Cup
in Bali from July 27 to August 3.
</P>
<P>
Pertina's deputy general secretary Didiet soedijoto said that
the home team would split into two teams, the Eagle Team and the
Hawk Team. The former includes those who are categorized as first
layer boxers.
</P>
<P>
"We are keeping a close eye, especially on the boxers in the
second layer because they will be guided for long-term training
commitments," Didiet was quoted by the Indonesian Observer Friday
as saying.
</P>
<P>
As many as 20 countries with a total of 139 boxers are said to
have confirmed their participation in the tournament, which is
held annually to coincide with Indonesia's Independence day.
</P>
<P>
The foreign countries who will join the tournament include
Japan who will come with seven boxers, Russia (8), England (7),
India (8), Germany (1), Malaysia (9), Iran (12), Brunei (1),
Australia (10), Laos (8), Thailand (3), Italy (7), Sri Lanka (7),
Mauritius (6), New Zealand (3), Nepal (4), Algeria (7) and
Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines, South Korea, Singapore, Uzbekistan, United
States, Canada and Netherlands have also confirmed but have yet to
specify the number of boxers they will send.
</P>
<P>
"The number of participants is a new record in the history of
the tournament. The previous competitions only saw 17 countries at
the most," Didiet added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
