<HEADLINE> New Zealand Slow in Transition to Online Business: Study </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 7 (Xinhua) -- A study released by ASB Bank
Friday said New Zealand has been slow to make the transition to
online business, and make economic gains from new technology and
the Internet.
</P>
<P>
The study said e-commerce has the potential to help New Zealand
overcome its two main disadvantages of geographic remoteness and
small size.
</P>
<P>
However it said few businesses in the country currently offer
online sales and purchasing.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand's economy is also still dependent on "old economy"
sectors such as agriculture, and the country is an importer rather
than a producer of high tech equipment, the study said. 
</P>
