<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0400 GMT, July 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- The euro zone industrial producer price index was 0.
8 percent higher in May compared to April, European Union (EU)
statistical office, Eurostat, reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The index had edged up by 0.1 percent in April. The 0.8 percent
increase was the highest since July 1999. The May increase stems
from the intermediate goods sector which advanced 1.2 percent in
the euro zone. (Euro Zone-Price)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Rolls-Royce plc announced Thursday that it has agreed
to extend its successful technology, services and consulting
relationship with EDS.
</P>
<P>
Rolls-Royce has awarded EDS 2.1 billion US dollars contract to
provide global information technology services and business
solutions, covering e-business, consulting and supply chain
management. (Rolls-Royce-Awards)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Paraguay's external debt reached 2.185 billion
U.S. dollars till May 31, increasing by 650 million dollars
compared to the beginning of year 2000, reported Thursday Central
Bank (BCP).
</P>
<P>
Paraguay's reserves were at 1 billion dollars on May 31, which
represents an increase of little over 18 million dollars relative
to April. The level of external deposits stayed at little over
945 million dollars relative to Paraguay's external debt. (
Paragua-Debt)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Latin American oil and natural gas companies
said Thursday that, at regional level, the sector will receive
private investment for 200 billion U.S. dollars in the next 10
years.
</P>
<P>
Milton Costa Filho, president of the Oil and Natural Gas
Companies Association, said that during 1999 Latin America
received a total of 70 billion dollars foreign investment, of
which 16 billion for the oil sector. (L. America-Oil)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
YANGON -- Myanmar produced 177,375 tons of cotton in the fiscal
year 1999-2000 which ended in March against the target of 198,000
tons, official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The tonnage was produced out of a cultivated area of 341,820
hectares but the production target was not reached as it rained
abnormally in November last year, the non-rainy season, Myanmar
Minister of Agriculture and Irrigation Major-General Nyunt Tin was
quoted as saying. (Myanmar-Cotton) 
