<HEADLINE> ASEAN Experts' Meetings End in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The two expert group meetings of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) on herbal and
medicinal plants, and on research and development for forest
products ended here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The two-day meetings, which began on Wednesday, discussed
matters respectively relating to technology transfer and trade
promotion in herbal and medicinal plants, and technology transfer
of wood products between ASEAN member countries and China.
</P>
<P>
The discussions also covered matters pertaining to a meeting of
the ASEAN senior officials on forestry, which will be the third
one, to be held here from next Monday to Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The meetings passed a decision to hold the next two meetings of
the ASEAN expert groups on herbal and medicinal plants, and on
research and development for forest products in the Philippines in
July 2001.
</P>
<P>
The meetings were attended by delegates from Brunei, Indonesia,
Laos, Malaysia, host Myanmar, the Philippines, Thailand and
Vietnam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
