<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yugoslav Assembly Approves Constitutional Amendments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The Yugoslav Federal Assembly on
Thursday approved major constitutional amendments concerning the
election and re-election of the president.
</P>
<P>
Under the amendments, the Yugoslav president will be directly
elected by the public, instead of by the Federal Assembly, and can
hold two terms of office.
</P>
<P>
Under the current constitution, the president's tenure is an
unrenewable four-year term.
</P>
<P>
Observers believe that the amendments have paved the way for
President Slobodan Milosevic's re-election after his current term
of office expires in 2001.
</P>
<P>
The amendments were endorsed by both chambers of parliament --
the Chamber of Citizens and the Chamber of Republics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
