<HEADLINE> Giovanni Trapattoni Named New Italian Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ROME, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Giovanni Trapattoni was named as the
new national coach by the Italian Football Federation here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Trapattoni takes over from Dino Zoff who resigned on Tuesday
after lost 2-1 to France in extra time in the final of Euro 2000
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Trapattoni has won eight league titles, one European Cup, the
UEFA Cup three times and the Cup Winners Cup once during spells at
AC Milan, Juventus and Inter Milan.
</P>
<P>
The 61-year-old also won the German Bundesliga in 1997 at
Bayern Munich before taking Fiorentina into the Champions League
in 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
