<HEADLINE> Guangzhou to Host International Expo of Building Materials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 7 (Xinhua) -- An international exposition of
building materials will be held on July 10-13 at this capital city
of south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The annual event has attracted 783 firms from China, the United
States, Japan, Italy and Canada to display their latest products,
including bathroom utensils, wooden floor, stone and glass
materials, ceramics, carpets, paint, kitchen utensils and hotel
equipment.
</P>
<P>
The exposition, jointly sponsored by the China Foreign Trade
Center (Group) and the China Council for the Promotion of
International Trade, has become one of the biggest expositions of
building materials in Asia since its debut in 1999.
</P>
<P>
A symposium on industrialization of residential buildings and
the application of environment-friendly building materials in the
21st century will also be held during the event. 
</P>
