<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Hails Good Prospects for Resumption of Syrian-Israeli Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Russia said Friday that it is
optimistic about the prospects for the resumption of the peace
talks between Syria and Israel, but "does not seek to synchronize
the progress of the Middle East settlement in all directions."
</P>
<P>
"Every track of the Middle East settlement has its special
problems, and therefore it is important that movement forward be
maintained in principle and concrete results be reached, even if
the paces of the progress are different on different tracks,"
Russian presidential envoy for the Middle East peace, deputy
Foreign Minister Vasily Sredin told the press here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The sooner breakthrough is achieved, both in the Syrian and
Palestinian directions, the sooner a just and stable peace will be
settled in the Middle East, Sredin stated.
</P>
<P>
Moscow believes that "the possibility of the resumption of
Syrian-Israeli negotiations and progress on this track still
remains,"because the parties "have already managed to find common
ground on many problems of settlement," he said.
</P>
<P>
He urged the parties to resolve the rest issues on the
principle of"full peace for full withdrawal", including returning
all the Golan Heights to Syria, working out proper security
measures and setting up normal peaceful relations between the two
states.
</P>
<P>
He expressed conviction that the new Syrian leadership headed
by Bashar al- Assad will remain devoted to the course towards
achieving a just peace with Israel."
</P>
<P>
Russia, "as a co-sponsor of the Middle East peace progress,
will do its best to attain this historic goal," the diplomat
stressed.
</P>
</TEXT>
