<HEADLINE> Europe's Leading Stocks Gain Amid Easing Concerns on US Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
London's FTSE 100 benchmark ended at 6497.5 points, a gain of 1.
2 percent on the day and 2.9 percent on the week, with advancing
shares outpacing the decliners by nearly two to one.
</P>
<P>
Computer consultant Logica rose 4.5 percent, rebounding from a
loss the previous session. Rival consultant CMG rose 3.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
