Fishing is the most active sector in Peru, with a growth of 31
percent in May, said the Institute said, attributing the lifting
of a ban on anchovy fishing.
</P>
<P>
The government has planned a growth between 4 percent and 6
percent this year, compared to 1.4 percent last year. 
</P>
