<HEADLINE> Peru's Tourism Income Up Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The state's Peruvian Promotion Commission (Promperu) said that
the 156 million dollars earned from tourism in 1992 went up to 1
billion dollars in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The source said that tourism contributes a total of 100 million
dollars a year to tax revenue from general taxes and from
consuming.
</P>
<P>
Tourism creates jobs, said Promperu. The sector employs 350,000
people, about 4.9 percent of the economically active population,
and 13 percent of the total jobs generated by the services sector.
</P>
<P>
The Peruvian government plans foresee to surpass this year one
million tourists received, after last year's figure of 900,000
foreign visitors.
</P>
<P>
The government goal for 2005 is to receive 2.5 million tourists.
</P>
