<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico Destroys 21 Tons of Marihuana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Over 21 tons of marihuana
plants cultivated in several points of Mexico's western state of
Michoacan were destroyed during the first six months of this year,
said the State Attorney Office (PGJE) on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Eighteen firearms, 13 of them long and five short, as well as
270 rounds of ammunition of different calibers, 18 kilos of
marihuana seeds were seized, and 44 persons were detained, said
the PGJE in a communique.
</P>
<P>
Ministerial agents and officials of the Experts Services
Direction took part in those operations, with the assistance of
helicopters of the PGJE, which made easier the finding of the
cultives and the places where the drug was processed.
</P>
<P>
The PGJE said that most of the seizures were made in small
communities of Morelia, Apatzingan, Lazaro Cardenas, Uruapan,
Zamora, and Zitacuaro, where the marihuana plants reached a height
of three meters.
</P>
<P>
Racks to dry the plants and installations to package the drug
with presses and other instruments were found in some places,
added the PGJE.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
