<HEADLINE> Brazil's Central Bank Cuts Interest Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Central Bank (BC) of Brazil
announced Friday it had reduced its basic rate of interest from 17.
5 percent to 17 percent per year.
</P>
<P>
The 0.5 percent cut to the basic rate of interest is the BC
third time cutting . The other two occurred in March and June,
respectively, reducing the basic rate of interest for a total of 1.
5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The successive reduction of the rates of interest is the result
of the economic and financial stability maintained by Brazil
during the first semester of the year, and will contribute to
accelerate the rhythm of economic recovery of the country, said
analysts.  
</P>
