<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan to Return Nuclear Fuel to Britain - Paper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A British newspaper said on Friday
that Britain is set to take back nuclear fuel from Japan, months
after the state-owned British Nuclear Fuels Ltd (BNFL) admitted
providing wrong specifications for the shipment.
</P>
<P>
A high-level meeting between the British and Japanese
governments has been scheduled for Tuesday, when they are expected
to agree the shipment should be returned, the Independent
newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The taking back will cost British taxpayers millions of pounds,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
"We are close to agreement with the British government on the
return of the fuel," the report quoted Takeo Hiranuma, Japan's
Minister of International Trade and Industry, as saying.
</P>
<P>
In February, Britain's nuclear watchdog released a report on
the shipment, saying there had been "a systematic management
failure" at BNFL. 
</P>
</TEXT>
